>&gt; Rebuilding it removes kernel.release first and then recreates it. This<br />&gt; might race with another parallel make job running depmod.<br />&gt;<br />&gt; So on arm and maybe other archs we need the same as for x86:<br />&gt;<br />&gt;  1648e4f8 x86, kbuild: make "make install" not depend on vmlinux<br />&gt;<br />&gt; The patch below fixes this for arm. It is build-tested in my<br />&gt; environment, but please test it in others too if possible.<br /><br />Ack. This looks like the right thing to do.<br /><br />That said, I think for clarity you might perhaps want to make the<br />unrelated change of adding double quotes around $(KERNELRELEASE) a<br />separate patch. Not a big deal, but it took me a moment to say "why<br />did he do that" (in fact, I'm not sure KERNEL_RELEASE can actually<br />validly have spaces in it, but quoting it is certainly not wrong<br />either - but it might be unnecessary.<br /><br />              Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
